The paper discusses privacy infrastructures and their vulnerabilities, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also touches upon the use of cryptographic tools and anonymity networks, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the potential harm caused by cyber criminals, which is relevant to the sub-categories of security and privacy (cs.SI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) as these areas deal with the management and protection of large-scale systems.
